Thanks for the error report and logs, really appreciate it. Sorry it took so long to check it out![:confused:](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif ":confused:")

I found the problem, I forgot to assign an input to one of my error log messages![:blush:](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif ":blush:"). Following that, the error message was for duplicate nodes. You could get the error when, for example, you have the CTT and ETT both installed. Since a bunch of people complained about duplicate nodes in the CTT forum in the past, I purposefully make the mod throw an error so the Player can sort it out manually or inform the modder.

So you have duplicate nodes in your <abbr title="Module Manager (mod)">MM</abbr> tech tree. I can't tell you which mods add the same nodes, but the error message should work now and at least tell you which node is duplicated (just the first duplicate node though, there might be more than one!). Download from below.

There's another bug with the zoom options now that I want to fix too before a new release.
